<p>In order to encourage better style wouldn&#8217;t it be reasonable idea to evaluate emails (by <span class="caps">URL</span> for e.g.) for good practises such as:</p>

<ul>
<li>No top posting</li>
<li>No spelling mistakes</li>
<li>Grammar check</li>
<li>Some sort of readability check</li>
<li>Proper attribution</li>
<li>Proper quoting</li>
<li>Careful editing</li>
<li>Line width maintained</li>
<li>text/plain</li>
<li><span class="caps">GPG</span> signature</li>
<li>Using a respectable <span class="caps">ISP</span></li>
<li>Award points for <span class="caps">MUA</span></li>
<li>Perhaps subtract points for vulnerable software detected</li>
<li>Proper encoding (unicode)</li>
<li>No rhetorical questions.</li>
<li>NO <span class="caps">CAPS</span></li>
<li>No abuse of smilies or punctuation</li>
<li>Not too long</li>
<li>Good use of paragraphs</li>
<li>No stupid signatures</li>
<li>Nothing offensive</li>
<li>No whitespace</li>
</ul>

<p>Feel free to add in the comments&#8230;</p>